Citation.sTitle: Density of molten sulfur in the 334 508K range
Citation.sAbstract: As the density of elemental sulfur was determined on slowly cooling from 508 K, it was unexpected for the metastable molten state to be maintained to temperatures as low as 334 K, thus expanding by about 20K the T-range within which experimental data become available.
